The '''Dandong shooting incident''' occurred when [[North Korean]] border guards shot dead three Chinese citizens and injured one at [[Dandong]] city [[Liaoning province]], [[People's Republic of China]] on June 4, 2010.

==Incident==
On June 4, 2010, four Chinese citizens were shot on suspicion of crossing the PRC&ndash;NK border for trade activities.  Three died and one was injured.  Qin Gang (<U+79E6><U+521A>), spokesman for [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the People's Republic of China|Ministry of Foreign Affairs]] publicised the news on June 8.<ref>Nasdaq.com. "[http://www.nasdaq.com/aspx/stock-market-news-story.aspx?storyid=201006080444dowjonesdjonline000123&title=chinanorth-korea-shot-dead-3-chinese-residents-at-border-friday Nasdaq.com]." ''North Korea Shot Dead 3 Chinese Residents At Border Friday.'' Retrieved on 2010-06-08.</ref><ref>Abc.net.au. "[http://www.abc.net.au/news/stories/2010/06/08/2921968.htm?section=world Abc.net.au]." ''North korean guards kill 3 at border.'' Retrieved on 2010-06-08.</ref><ref>Libertytimes.com.tw. "[http://iservice.libertytimes.com.tw/liveNews/news.php?no=373907&type=%E5%9C%8B%E9%9A%9B Libertytimes.com.tw]." ''<U+4E2D><U+570B><U+8D8A><U+754C><U+8CBF><U+6613><U+3000><U+5317><U+97D3><U+99D0><U+8ECD><U+958B><U+706B>3<U+6B7B>.'' Retrieved on 2010-06-08.</ref>  According to [[South Korean]] media reports, the people shot were members of a Dandong smuggling group on a ship on [[Yalu River]].  Cross-border smuggling is a common occurrence since North Korea is short on commodities supplies.<ref>South China Morning Post. "[http://www.scmp.com/portal/site/SCMP/menuitem.2af62ecb329d3d7733492d9253a0a0a0/?vgnextoid=8f84bc46f7819210VgnVCM100000360a0a0aRCRD&ss=China&s=News SCMP]." ''China protests to N Korea after 3 shot dead at border.'' Retrieved on 2010-06-07.</ref>  The North Korean soldiers may have fired suspecting the Chinese citizens were South Korean spies after the South became more cautious due to the [[ROKS Cheonan sinking]].<ref>Big5.ifeng.com. "[http://big5.ifeng.com/gate/big5/news.ifeng.com/mainland/detail_2010_06/09/1603024_0.shtml Big5.ifeng.com]." ''<U+5317><U+97D3><U+5C31><U+5C04><U+6BBA><U+4E2D><U+570B><U+4EBA><U+4E8B><U+4EF6><U+4F5C><U+51FA><U+89E3><U+91CB> <U+9858><U+610F><U+64AB><U+6064><U+6B7B><U+50B7><U+8005><U+5BB6><U+5C6C>.'' Retrieved on 2010-06-07.</ref>  NK authorities said they were willing to compensate the families of those killed so as not to harm [[People's Republic of China <U+2013> North Korea relations|Sino-NK relations]].<ref>Timesonline.co.uk. "[http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/world/asia/article7146516.ece Timesonline.co.uk]." ''Chinese killed by NK border guards.'' Retrieved on 2010-06-07.</ref>

==Other recent incidents==
In 2008, a South Korean tourist was shot by North korean soldiers at the [[K<U+016D>mgangsan Tourist Region]].  In October 2009, [[Chinese special forces]] detected [[sarin]] poision gas in the air at the North Korea&ndash;PRC border.<ref>[http://news.hkheadline.com/instantnews/news_content/200910/09/20091009e150346.html?cat=e news.hkheadline.com special forces detect sarin in air]</ref>

